{
  "texts": [
    "The study included 196 participants, consisting of 196 participants for the quantitative survey and 15 for the qualitative interviews.",
    "The survey participants were distributed across age groups: 18-22, 23-26, 27-30, and 31-35. Gender distribution was also approximately balanced.",
    "Two sampling methods were applied, consistent with the mixed-methods approach.",
    "Stratified Random Sampling involves dividing the population into distinct subgroups (strata) based on age and gender and randomly selecting participants from each subset.",
    "The Stratified Random Sampling technique ensures proportional representation and reduces sampling bias (Etikan & Bala, 2017)."
  ]
}